Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.92,0:00:05.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Star" is a fascinating word.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.50,0:00:07.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can refer to both culprits and actors!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.29,0:00:09.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today's case has a different taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.22,0:00:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be solving three different-flavored tricks...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.84,0:00:12.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And savoring the pleasing feeling of solving a mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.76,0:00:14.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing through to the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.43,0:00:16.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I look like a child, but have the intellect of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.10,0:00:18.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My name is Detective Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.21,0:00:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, we felt the same light the moment we met.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.10,0:00:29.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, lots and lots of the same emotions filled our eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.85,0:00:35.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although the signals you sent destroyed my theory...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.75,0:00:41.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These feelings were always beyond your reach
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.74,0:00:47.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, let's fight, go against our morals...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.78,0:00:52.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And aim for a wider world!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.30,0:00:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, glimmering star, shine over us forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.15,0:01:05.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, we won't lose the dreams we had when we were young...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.13,0:01:11.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't care if this town changes someday.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.10,0:01:17.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing I don't want to change is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.20,0:01:23.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, glimmering star, shine over us forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.90,0:01:29.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, we won't lose the dreams we had when we were young...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.00,0:01:39.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing I don't want to change is you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.22,0:01:46.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of problem could you have to sigh about?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.14,0:01:50.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I was just wondering if\NRan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} is doing okay in her karate match.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.69,0:01:53.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course she's doing fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.07,0:01:55.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She practiced all day yesterday, on top of going to bed early.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.03,0:01:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's in great shape!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.95,0:01:59.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.12,0:02:01.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.62,0:02:03.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.73,0:02:06.75,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Like I've been telling you all along...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.83,0:02:07.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that the lady from the\NYuuzuki Japanese-style confection shop?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.21,0:02:09.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police officer must be Kinoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.92,0:02:11.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, is there a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.88,0:02:14.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you came at a great time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.34,0:02:17.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please listen to this, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.81,0:02:21.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, we have a problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.05,0:02:21.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.95,0:02:24.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.35,0:02:27.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have a bad feeling about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.06,0:02:31.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Spicy, Bitter & Sweet Soup!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.05,0:02:37.99,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,In other words, what both of you are trying to say is...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.77,0:02:42.96,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,350)} Aikawa Etsuko (58)\N"Yuuzuki" Japanese-style Confection Shop Owner
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.43,0:02:43.51,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Is that you, Madam, saw a man run out\Nof the first-floor apartment, number 1055.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.70,0:02:46.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just said you saw this occur two hours ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.00,0:02:48.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means it was about 9:00 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.62,0:02:53.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that was when you came to\Ntake her statement, Kinoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.08,0:02:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.92,0:02:58.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then Kinoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} found the body of\Nthe room's owner, Ozawa Fumie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.42,0:03:01.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And concluded it was a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.18,0:03:02.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be a suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.89,0:03:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.72,0:03:08.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you see, I saw the crime scene with my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.64,0:03:11.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had a will, and there wasn't\Nany sign of a struggle in her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.69,0:03:12.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.48,0:03:18.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, there aren't any other\Nwitnesses for that mysterious person you saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.94,0:03:21.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure I saw him with my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.86,0:03:22.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.66,0:03:27.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please tell him to check more thoroughly, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.04,0:03:27.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.24,0:03:29.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.00,0:03:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what makes you think it was suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.96,0:03:37.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just to be sure, I asked a medical\Nexaminer to come investigate that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.96,0:03:41.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging by the amount of rigor mortis that\Nhas set in, we estimate her time of death to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.80,0:03:45.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,6:00 to 8:00 PM last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.10,0:03:48.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the suspicious person killed him like this woman says...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.68,0:03:51.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would have had to remain in the victim's room for...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.39,0:03:55.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,13 hours after he killed her, without\Ntouching anything so it would look like a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.23,0:03:57.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you think about it logically, that's unthinkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.73,0:03:59.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You guys can't get your nose out of your notepads...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.86,0:04:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So let's have Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} decide the cause of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.99,0:04:04.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I'm begging you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.51,0:04:06.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.16,0:04:07.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is so troubling...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.16,0:04:11.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your face doesn't look the least bit troubled to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.92,0:04:24.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kinoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.43,0:04:26.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the man I saw!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.68,0:04:27.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sure of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.35,0:04:30.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, please don't touch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.06,0:04:30.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.44,0:04:36.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim was...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.02,0:04:38.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The owner of this room,\NOzawa Fumie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, 24 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.90,0:04:41.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was a secretary who worked for a trading company.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.61,0:04:44.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I discovered her body...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.24,0:04:47.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I noticed she had tied a wire to the\Nshower head and wrapped it around her neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.70,0:04:51.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looked like she was leaning\Nagainst the wall while sitting down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.70,0:04:55.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a pretty unusual place for a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.46,0:04:56.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, please take a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.84,0:05:00.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She wrote her will on her laptop computer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.34,0:05:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"To the one I'm loaning to, Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}..."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.72,0:05:09.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I know how much I've troubled you,\Nso I will repent for my sin by dying."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.14,0:05:11.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The contents of the will say...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.60,0:05:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That she spent over 30 million\Nyen of her company's money...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.93,0:05:16.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And wanted to repent by killing herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.69,0:05:18.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears the will was written to her superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.90,0:05:20.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Embezzlement, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.73,0:05:24.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She sent it via e-mail at 5:45 PM yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.65,0:05:27.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We believe she killed herself shortly after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.71,0:05:42.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go meddle around somewhere else!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.01,0:05:48.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She put it on vibrate? Even when she's in her house?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.39,0:05:57.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've come to the conclusion that it's\Na suicide, just as Kinoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} says.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.31,0:06:00.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please take a look at the calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.31,0:06:02.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't there a dentist appointment on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.15,0:06:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Calendar?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.41,0:06:12.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true that it says she had a\Ndentist appointment scheduled for today...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.41,0:06:16.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Madam, you must have really good eyesight...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.20,0:06:18.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you were able to read this from all the way over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.29,0:06:21.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah... I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.58,0:06:25.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she planned her suicide this precisely,\Neven preparing the wires to hang herself...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.05,0:06:28.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would she really have scheduled a\Ndentist appointment the same day?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.26,0:06:29.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.39,0:06:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kinoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, could this really be possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.85,0:06:38.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought, this is a murder\Ncommitted by the man in that picture, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.77,0:06:41.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not sure about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.48,0:06:46.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kinoshita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was the house\Nunlocked when you first arrived here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.90,0:06:49.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, the house was unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.70,0:06:51.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.11,0:06:53.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She committed suicide without locking the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.37,0:06:54.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.24,0:06:58.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone committing a well-planned suicide\Nwouldn't want to be found before they died.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.71,0:07:01.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The picture by the front door must\Nhave been taken out of this photo album.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.83,0:07:02.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.96,0:07:04.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.13,0:07:04.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.88,0:07:09.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lady who died must have\Nbeen close to the man in this picture...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.01,0:07:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder why she didn't address her will to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.55,0:07:13.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, le le?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.26,0:07:16.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle, whatever could this be?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.22,0:07:19.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's some white powder or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.82,0:07:28.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.12,0:07:46.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it's a powder that\Ndoesn't smell, feels silky, and is edible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.80,0:07:56.10,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: Katakuri starch is an ingredient made from the stems of katakuri lilies.\NIt's used a thickener, but has the sweetness of powdered/confectioner's sugar.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.09,0:07:50.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is probably katakuri starch.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.09,0:07:53.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What else can you do with\Nkatakuri starch besides using it in cooking?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.68,0:07:55.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me think...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.30,0:07:56.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can use it on sweets.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.25,0:08:01.80,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: A daifuku is a Japanese confection consisting of a\Nsmall, round mochi (rice cake) stuffed with sweet filling.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.81,0:07:58.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know the powder that daifuku are coated with?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.68,0:08:00.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's katakuri starch.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.39,0:08:05.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, the company that Ozawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was working for...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.48,0:08:07.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Reported that it has 30 million yen deficit...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.52,0:08:11.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that the victim's superior,\NShimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, took a day off today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.49,0:08:15.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he doesn't know that Ozawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} committed suicide yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.66,0:08:19.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, we discovered something unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.54,0:08:23.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man holding the cooler box\Nis the one who got the e-mail...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.87,0:08:25.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And is also her superior, Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.92,0:08:27.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the supervisor was her lover?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.46,0:08:32.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems that none of the\Nemployees knew they were dating.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.80,0:08:38.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it seems that Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} enjoys\Ngambling and making hefty investments.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.72,0:08:41.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, doesn't something smell fishy to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.85,0:08:44.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.56,0:08:48.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.52,0:08:50.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the one who ran out of the room!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.65,0:08:52.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You better explain what happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.07,0:08:54.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.82,0:08:56.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.70,0:08:58.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Move away! Don't bother him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.27,0:08:59.90,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It's this guy! It'd him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.28,0:09:01.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, this is Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.08,0:09:04.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was resting at his house, and we asked him to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.34,0:09:14.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll get right down to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.84,0:09:16.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You knew that one of your subordinates, Ozawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.72,0:09:19.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Embezzled 30 million yen out of your company.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.35,0:09:20.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.60,0:09:25.05,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Shimizu Ryota (30)\NChief Executive of a Consumer Loan Company
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.64,0:09:24.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I only found out from the police officers earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.02,0:09:25.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.31,0:09:30.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Weren't you Ozawa Fumie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s lover?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.11,0:09:32.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would think that you'd discuss\Nthings like that with each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.57,0:09:34.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lovers?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.49,0:09:37.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, that picture the police officers asked me about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.57,0:09:40.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was when Ozawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} wanted to go on a fishing trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.78,0:09:42.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I took her to the best spot I knew about.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.54,0:09:45.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were you today at 9:00 AM?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.04,0:09:47.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.62,0:09:51.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is a witness who saw you run out of this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.09,0:09:52.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saw me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.92,0:09:57.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't pretend you don't know! I saw you with my own eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.38,0:09:59.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to ask you bluntly.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.01,0:10:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you break into this room at 9:00 AM\Nthis morning, and murder Ozawa Fumie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.60,0:10:06.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You think I used Ozawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.60,0:10:09.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stole the money that she loaned...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.02,0:10:10.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then killed her?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.65,0:10:15.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, you took advantage of her\Nuntil you got everything you desired...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.74,0:10:16.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.57,0:10:18.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute. It can't be me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.24,0:10:23.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was attending my elementary school\Nclass reunion for the entire day yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.87,0:10:25.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At around 9:00 AM this morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.41,0:10:28.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was at at the airport, waiting for my\Nplane which departed for Haneda at 10:00 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.87,0:10:30.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here's my ticket for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.75,0:10:38.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, where were you between\N6:00 PM and 8:00 PM yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.05,0:10:40.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I said, I was in the middle of my reunion...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.84,0:10:42.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here's the organizer's business card.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.76,0:10:44.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll have to hold on to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.89,0:10:46.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.35,0:10:47.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please check it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.31,0:10:48.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.44,0:10:50.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has an alibi...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.81,0:10:53.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the lady said she's sure it was him who ran out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.36,0:10:55.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't suicide...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.77,0:11:00.25,Signs,,0,0,0,,6:00 PM-\NDentist\NAppointment
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.77,0:11:00.25,Signs,,0,0,0,,May Day
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.77,0:11:00.25,Signs,,0,0,0,,Constitution\NMemorial Day
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.77,0:11:00.25,Signs,,0,0,0,,Mother's day
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.55,0:11:18.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did they say?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.80,0:11:21.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything the man said was a lie, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.64,0:11:24.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just like Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.14,0:11:26.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Both the class reunion organizer...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.77,0:11:28.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the airline confirmed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.89,0:11:35.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! Maybe she just mistook Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} for somebody else.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.23,0:11:38.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she was able to read what\Nthe calendar said from far away...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.87,0:11:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she must have good eyesight, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.03,0:11:44.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, maybe she wanted to frame Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.32,0:11:45.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But for what reason...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.91,0:11:48.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have no idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.62,0:11:51.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, what happened to Horita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.04,0:11:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A deliveryman said he saw something...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.67,0:11:55.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he's questioning him at the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.67,0:11:59.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it seems like my alibi has been confirmed...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.21,0:12:01.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I'll be leaving now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.64,0:12:06.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.60,0:12:09.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't let this man go, he committed a murder!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.85,0:12:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Madam...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.39,0:12:13.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a bothersome person.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.14,0:12:15.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have a grudge against me or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.15,0:12:18.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any proof that I'm the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.61,0:12:19.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.03,0:12:23.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've known her since she was very little.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.91,0:12:27.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She treated me like her mother, and told me everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.37,0:12:30.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She told me how she was dating someone named Shimizu...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.66,0:12:34.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that he told her to loan\Nout a lot of the company's money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.58,0:12:36.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She confessed everything to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.67,0:12:38.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What on earth are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.26,0:12:43.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.80,0:12:50.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It really tickles me when it's on vibrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.81,0:12:52.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes? This is Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.68,0:12:54.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Medical examiner?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.10,0:12:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About what I requested?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.65,0:12:58.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There wasn't anything wrong\Nwith Ozawa fumie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s teeth?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.98,0:13:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she had a dentist appointment, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.78,0:13:04.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.95,0:13:08.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was nothing wrong with her,\Nbut had an appointment for the dentist, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.20,0:13:11.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, this might be unnecessary...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.37,0:13:14.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't the handwriting on the\Ncalendar different from Ozawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.33,0:13:19.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As her superior, I see her handwriting often.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.67,0:13:24.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, we're going to need expert to analyze them further...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.75,0:13:24.47,Signs,,0,0,0,,Appointment\Nat Yamada\NInternal\NMedicine
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.75,0:13:24.47,Signs,,0,0,0,,Appointment\Nat Izumi\NDermatology
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.47,0:13:26.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the two handwriting styles do appear to be different.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.51,0:13:29.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whose handwriting is on the calendar, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.39,0:13:35.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From what I heard, this woman was\Nthe first to discover the body, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.06,0:13:38.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, now I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.02,0:13:41.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The true culprit is often the first to arrive at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.19,0:13:45.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It sure is sad that Madam is the culprit, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.45,0:13:47.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.74,0:13:51.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Madam wanted to frame Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} as the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.28,0:13:55.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why she wrote that Fumie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nhad scheduled a dentist appointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.62,0:14:00.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's also why the picture was in the\Nentryway instead of its usual spot in the photo album.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.50,0:14:04.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Madam, just to be sure, could you please write "dentist"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.80,0:14:08.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure it was that woman over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.89,0:14:11.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm absolutely positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.30,0:14:13.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She hid it in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.02,0:14:20.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.48,0:14:22.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.23,0:14:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.28,0:14:25.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.90,0:14:28.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Madam...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.95,0:14:33.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You entered this room around 9:00 AM today, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.83,0:14:34.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.12,0:14:39.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a delivery man outside who\Nsays he saw you come out of this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.25,0:14:44.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, he said you were in a hurry,\Nwhich caused you to bump into him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.72,0:14:50.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is 5 million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.76,0:14:52.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did you get all this money?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.60,0:14:55.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And why did you hide it in the gas meter box?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.22,0:14:57.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you mind explaining?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.69,0:15:00.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I brought the money with me from my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.31,0:15:04.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hid the money in there\Nbecause I found Fumie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s body...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.27,0:15:08.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I was worried I might drop it\Non my way to report it to the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.36,0:15:09.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the only reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.70,0:15:12.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you really were in this room before, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.28,0:15:14.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I wasn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.33,0:15:18.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must have killed Ozawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nand then tried to frame me as the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.29,0:15:20.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.12,0:15:23.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, please don't believe what he's saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.21,0:15:24.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.38,0:15:25.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is troubling...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.17,0:15:27.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.55,0:15:29.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of them is lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.30,0:15:32.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of them is the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.18,0:15:39.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.73,0:15:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A fish scale?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.60,0:15:42.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would one be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.23,0:15:45.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.78,0:15:47.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.82,0:15:49.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's what happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.56,0:15:57.01,Signs,,0,0,0,,Dentist
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.62,0:16:00.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wrote the fake appointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.37,0:16:03.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I also put the photo in front of the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.08,0:16:06.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was it to frame Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} for your crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.09,0:16:07.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's not it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.92,0:16:10.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew Shimizu was the criminal,\Nand wanted to have him arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.76,0:16:13.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came here this morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.72,0:16:16.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To be with Fumie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} when she\Nconfessed about the money she had embezzled.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.47,0:16:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I also thought that if she\Nreturned what was left of the money...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.60,0:16:23.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She might get a lighter sentence,\Nso I brought the money with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.82,0:16:31.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I saw Fumie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s dead body,\Nand my instincts told me right away...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.40,0:16:33.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Shimizu was the one who had done that to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.86,0:16:37.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because she told me she would tell\Nthe police everything she had done.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.66,0:16:42.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there wasn't anything in this\Nroom that would get Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.92,0:16:45.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you decided to put his picture in\Nthe entryway, close to the front door...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.86,0:16:47.30,Signs,,0,0,0,,6:00 PM-\NDentist\NAppointment
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.86,0:16:47.30,Signs,,0,0,0,,May Day
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.86,0:16:47.30,Signs,,0,0,0,,Constitution\NMemorial Day
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.86,0:16:47.30,Signs,,0,0,0,,Mother's day
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.38,0:16:47.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And wrote that false appointment on the calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.46,0:16:50.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is that man right there, Shimizu!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.80,0:16:56.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Madam, that's just your assumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.34,0:16:59.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have to take it with a grain of salt...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.01,0:17:01.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has an airtight alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.89,0:17:05.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm interested in hearing how you\Ncame into possession of that 5 million yen...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.94,0:17:07.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So would you please come with me to the police station?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.65,0:17:15.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, sorry to keep you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.11,0:17:17.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the iceman, Inoue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.62,0:17:20.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The iceman? What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.24,0:17:21.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're such a jokester...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.49,0:17:24.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like you thought, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...\NThat man really did buy ice from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.17,0:17:26.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, Korita{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.79,0:17:30.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the time being, take her down to the police\Nstation, and we can listen to what she has to say there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.46,0:17:31.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.31,0:17:48.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please hold off on doing that, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.44,0:17:50.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.07,0:17:51.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.98,0:17:52.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It finally started!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.98,0:17:56.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please release that woman immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.61,0:17:58.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who needs to be taken to the police station...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.16,0:18:01.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is you, Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.03,0:18:02.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why do I need to go to the police station?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.70,0:18:06.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inoue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, when did this man come to buy ice from you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.08,0:18:08.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yesterday afternoon...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.58,0:18:10.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He bought four packs of ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.59,0:18:11.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About 15 kilograms worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.17,0:18:15.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I remember him distinctly,\Nsince he had a big cooler box prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.97,0:18:18.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, during this season...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.22,0:18:21.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About how long does it take ice to melt?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.81,0:18:24.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At room temperature, probably about half a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.72,0:18:27.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks for helping out, even though\Nthis is the busiest time of the year for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.52,0:18:29.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Oh, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.52,0:18:32.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you for cooperating.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.61,0:18:35.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer Sato...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.99,0:18:39.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you look underneath the\Nbathtub cover, you'll find a fish scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.32,0:18:41.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please remove the wires from it and bring it here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.91,0:18:43.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A fish scale in the bathroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.12,0:18:46.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.25,0:18:48.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Around yesterday at noon...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.46,0:18:51.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You most likely gave Ozawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Na sleeping pill to put her sleep...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.13,0:18:52.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then carried her over to the bathtub.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.96,0:18:58.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You then made her sit on a chair you had put\Ntogether using the bathtub cover and the block of ice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.38,0:19:02.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As the ice melted, the seat got lower,\Ncausing the wires around her neck to tighten.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.26,0:19:06.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the time of her death, from 6:00 PM to 8:00 PM...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.44,0:19:08.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ice would have been less than half of its original size.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.29,0:19:11.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, by the time Madam found her...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.44,0:19:12.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ice had completely melted...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.90,0:19:15.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the water evaporated, leaving the floor completely dry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.94,0:19:19.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The scale we found on the bathtub cover...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.36,0:19:22.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Must have been from the cooler\Nbox you used to carry the ice in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.16,0:19:24.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I've been saying...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.24,0:19:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You still don't have any definitive evidence that I killed her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.91,0:19:31.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And did you forget?\NOzawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} sent me an e-mail at 5:45 PM!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.96,0:19:36.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could someone send me an e-mail if they\Nhad already been drugged and strangled with wires?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.26,0:19:42.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan, put Ozawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s cell phone\Nin the open space on the bookshelf...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.01,0:19:44.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And have half of it leaning over the side of the shelf.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.35,0:19:45.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.73,0:19:52.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.11,0:19:56.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cellphone is on vibrate right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.94,0:19:58.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer Sato...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.03,0:19:59.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please call Ozawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s cellphone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.40,0:20:01.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.75,0:20:14.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you look at the cellphone's call log...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.75,0:20:18.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There should be a record of a call just before 5:45 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.42,0:20:21.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, there's no way I could've done it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.59,0:20:22.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I was in Hiroshima.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.93,0:20:25.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't know when to give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.60,0:20:29.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer Sato, please take a close look at the wires.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.39,0:20:32.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are strands of hair stuck in them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.60,0:20:35.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there any other hair besides Ozawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.36,0:20:38.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.27,0:20:40.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a single strand of straight, black hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.11,0:20:42.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.15,0:20:44.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you carried Ozawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to the bathroom...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.74,0:20:47.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn't notice that some of your hair fell off onto hers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.45,0:20:50.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you know, if we analyzed it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.66,0:20:51.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shimizu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.71,0:20:54.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We could find out who it belongs to right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.67,0:21:00.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.67,0:21:04.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't let her waste the rest of her life in jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.72,0:21:06.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, before she could confess to the police...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.21,0:21:07.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.75,0:21:17.85,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: "Sweet soup" is a Japanese expression\Nmeaning "to make good out what one has."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.40,0:21:17.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had your taste of sweet soup...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.85,0:21:22.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: Megure makes it intro a pun by using\N"bitter soup" to represent "having hard times."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.15,0:21:21.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now, you'll be getting the bitter soup you deserve.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.81,0:21:59.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before I knew it, I had come to the riverside of memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.32,0:22:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Imagining a continuation of yesterday's dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.53,0:22:15.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You seemed so grown-up when you were a boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.16,0:22:21.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't say goodbye, so I hid under my umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.38,0:22:27.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we ever meet again, just please remember
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.05,0:22:31.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,all those times, and don't forget me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.55,0:22:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My love and affection are things that will never change.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.82,0:22:52.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You are my one and only love, and that's how it will always be.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.62,0:23:02.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like many people, I reminisce while holding on to my feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.38,0:23:14.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I can keep the memory of us meeting from fading away.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.89,0:23:21.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, that really was incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.98,0:23:24.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Inspector Megure said\Nthat move was a stroke of genius!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.86,0:23:29.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You pretended you didn't think it was\NShimizu, so he would fall right into your trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.77,0:23:34.05,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: This is an old Japanese expression meaning\N"To trick someone, you first need to pretend to be tricked."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.99,0:23:31.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's often said that, to taste sweetness...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.49,0:23:34.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You first need to taste something salty.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.05,0:23:40.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,Note: Japanese men simply can't tolerate eating sweets,\Nwhich is why Mouri gags when eating one.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.62,0:23:44.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you need to eat something salty too?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.88,0:23:52.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They sure are ringing a long time...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.93,0:23:55.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that case from 12 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.68,0:23:57.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was one, 12 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.81,0:24:00.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A case where the same method\Nas in our current case was used.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.69,0:24:04.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that mean it's from Ran?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.40,0:24:06.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, could that mean that...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.94,0:24:08.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could that mean that...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.40,0:24:09.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't good!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.24,0:24:14.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan: The Weird Family's Request, Part 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.99,0:24:18.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.58,0:24:20.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cell phone's lock.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.08,0:24:26.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please look forward to the next episode!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.15,0:24:22.30,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hey, where's Officer Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.32,0:24:23.99,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,He's not here because the title is "Sweet Soup."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.06,0:24:25.26,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Sato{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.26,0:24:25.69,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Eh?
